[Black "Word of Thanks"]
[Result "*"]

{ First of all I would like to thank my brother Peter Mesotten for compiling the extensive list of more than 2,500 variations. This saved me a huge amount of time, allowing me to focus mainly on the quality of each exercise.  Thanks to the fantastic testing work of deepakbisth, Hermione117 and MichelT, the level of this course in terms of content, usability and linguistics increased a lot. Thank you very much!  Thank you to chessable for the opportunity to publish books as an amateur chess player. And of course a big thank you to IM Andras Toth for doing the videos and for taking the whole course to the next level! If you want to see a passionate chess player, coach and entertainer in action, make sure to check out his twitch channel: chesscoachandras.  Thanks to Simon and Mark from Youtube channel Cracking The Cryptic for keeping me entertained with Sudokus and puzzle games like 'The Witness' and 'Baba Is You' after long days composing chess puzzles.  And last but not least, I would like to thank my girlfriend Tania. For two months my first love, chess, came first  (again)  ... If you would like to be inspired about healthy food, follow her on Instagram: @tania_health.  Happy chess,  Raf Mesotten aka CraftyRaf }
