[White "2. Ruy López, Morphy Defense (3... a6)"]
[Black "Ruy López, Morphy Defense, Exchange Variation, Lutikov Variation (1)"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 { Ruy López } 3... a6 { Morphy Defense } 4. Bxc6
{ Exchange Variation } 4... bxc6
{ Lutikov Variation, A rather dubious move, since the light-squared Bishop is still trapped behind it's own pawns. }
5. O-O Nf6 { Developing the Knight while attacking  e4  , a poor move... } 6.
Nxe5 { The best move: Grabbing Black's center pawn. } 6... Nxe4
{ Another blunder, opening up the e-file while Black's King still hasn't castled yet. }
7. Re1 { Making use of the open e-file, attacking the Knight on  e4  . } 7...
d5 { Defending the Knight. } 8. d3
{ Attacking the Knight. A possible continuation is  8...Nf6  9.Nxc6+  , losing the Queen @@StartBracket@@+8.5@@EndBracket@@. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "2. Ruy López, Morphy Defense (3... a6)"]
[Black "Ruy López, Morphy Defense, Exchange Variation, Lutikov Variation (2)"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 { Ruy López } 3... a6 { Morphy Defense } 4. Bxc6
{ Exchange Variation } 4... bxc6
{ Lutikov Variation, A rather dubious move, since the light-squared Bishop is still trapped behind it's own pawns. }
5. O-O d6 { Defending  e5  . } 6. d4 { Challenging Black's center. } 6... Bg4
{ Pinning the Knight to the Queen, right? } 7. dxe5
{ Opening up the d-file for the Queen. } 7... dxe5
{ Another poor move  (played hundreds of times)  , to illustrate what could go wrong for Black. }
8. Qxd8+ Rxd8 9. Nxe5
{ Because the Queen is gone, the Knight isn't pinned anymore @@StartBracket@@+2.0@@EndBracket@@. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "2. Ruy López, Morphy Defense (3... a6)"]
[Black "Ruy López, Morphy Defense, Exchange Variation, Lutikov Variation (3)"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 { Ruy López } 3... a6 { Morphy Defense } 4. Bxc6
{ Exchange Variation } 4... bxc6
{ Lutikov Variation, A rather dubious move, since the light-squared Bishop is still trapped behind it's own pawns. }
5. Nxe5
{ This move is played thousands of times... But it's not that good, mainly because of  5...Qe7  or  5...Qg5  , activating the Queen with tempo. }
5... Nf6 { Developing the Knight, attacking  e4  . } 6. Nc3
{ Defending  e4  , although  6.O-O  would have been better. } 6... Qe7
{ 6...Qe7  is a decent move before both Knights are out. But not in this position. }
7. d4 { Defending the Knight on  e5  . } 7... d6
{ Attacking the Knight, but forgetting about the pawn on  c6  ... } 8. Nxc6
{ This is the point. Without Knights on  c3  and  f6  , Black's Queen could now capture  e4  with check. This move is not an option in this variation. White just won two pawns for free @@StartBracket@@+3.0@@EndBracket@@. }
*

