[White "2. Ruy López, Morphy Defense (3... a6)"]
[Black "Ruy López, Morphy Defense, Exchange Variation, Normal Variation (3)"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 { Ruy López } 3... a6 { Morphy Defense } 4. Bxc6
{ Exchange Variation } 4... dxc6 5. O-O { Normal Variation } 5... Bg4
{ Attacking the Knight on f3 while pinning it to the Queen. } 6. h3
{ Chasing away the Bishop. } 6... Bh5 7. g4
{ Unpinning the Knight on  f3  , so it is free to capture the pawn on  e5  . }
7... Bg6 8. Nxe5 Bxe4 { A very poor move. } 9. Re1
{ Developing the Rook, eyeing at Black's King.   If the Bishop moves e.g.  9...Bd5  , White can give a discovered check  10.Nxc6+  , winning Black's Queen next move. }
9... Qd5
{ Defending the Bishop while attacking White's Knight. This move makes things worse for Black. }
10. Nc3 { Forking Queen and Bishop. } 10... Qxe5 11. Rxe4
{ White is winning the Queen and the game @@StartBracket@@+6.0@@EndBracket@@. }
