1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 { Ruy López } 3... a6 { Morphy Defense } 4. Bxc6
{ Exchange Variation } 4... dxc6 5. O-O { Normal Variation } 5... Bd6
{ King's Bishop Variation } 6. h3 { Preventing Bg4. } 6... Nf6 7. Re1 O-O 8. d4
{ Challenging Black's center. } 8... Re8
{ Defending the pawn on  e5  , right?   You will see soon why  8...Nd7  was a better move to defend  e5  @@StartBracket@@+0.0@@EndBracket@@. }
9. dxe5 { Grabbing a center pawn while forking Bishop and Knight. } 9... Bxe5
{ Most players capture the pawn on  e5  . The Rook is overloaded: It has to guard both the Queen and the Bishop in the center of the board. }
10. Qxd8 { Trading Queens. } 10... Rxd8 11. Nxe5
{ Capturing a free Bishop. White is up a piece @@StartBracket@@+5.5@@EndBracket@@. }
