[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 { Ruy López } 3... a6 { Morphy Defense } 4. Bxc6
{ Exchange Variation } 4... dxc6 5. O-O { Normal Variation } 5... Bd6
{ King's Bishop Variation } 6. d4 { Challenging Black's center. } 6... f6
{ Defending  e5  even more. This is a poor move. } 7. dxe5
{ Trading a pair of center pawns. } 7... fxe5
{ Black almost always recaptures with the pawn, that's why he played f6 in the first place. }
8. Nxe5 { A strong Knight sacrifice! } 8... Qh4
{ An interesting move, attacking  e4  while eyeing on  h2  with the Queen. Note that the Bishop still attacks the Knight in the center.   8...Bxe5  would make things worse because of  9.Qh5+  , losing both the Bishop and the opportunity to castle. }
9. Nf3
{ Bringing the Knight to a safer square while guarding h2 and chasing away the Queen @@StartBracket@@+1.5@@EndBracket@@.   9...Qxe4  isn't a threat because of  10.Re1  . }
