[White "2. Ruy López, Morphy Defense (3... a6)"]
[Black "Ruy López, Morphy Defense, Exchange Variation, Normal Variation, King's Bishop Variation (4)"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 { Ruy López } 3... a6 { Morphy Defense } 4. Bxc6
{ Exchange Variation } 4... dxc6 5. O-O { Normal Variation } 5... Bd6
{ King's Bishop Variation } 6. d4 { Challenging Black's center. } 6... Bg4
{ An inaccurate move: Attacking the Knight and pinning it to the Queen. But how can you take advantage of it? }
7. dxe5 { Trading a pair of center pawns, opening up the d-file. } 7... Bxe5
{ A big blunder...   The normal continuation in this position is  7...Bxf3  8.Qxf3  Bxe5  , with a slight advantage for White @@StartBracket@@+1.0@@EndBracket@@. }
8. Qxd8+ { Trading Queens. } 8... Rxd8 9. Nxe5
{ And now we can take the Bishop for free! The Knight now isn't pinned anymore because we traded Queens one move earlier. White is far ahead @@StartBracket@@+6.0@@EndBracket@@. }
