1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 { Ruy López } 3... Nf6 { Berlin Defense } 4. O-O
Nxe4 { Rio Gambit Accepted } 5. Re1
{ Occupying the semi-open e-file, attacking the Knight. } 5... d5
{ Protecting the Knight. This blunder has been played thousands of times! } 6.
d3 { Kicking away the Knight on  e4  , opening the file for the Rook. } 6...
Nd6
{ The most played move in this position. All other moves are bad as well, e.g.  6...Nf6  7.Nxe5  Be6  8.Nxc6  @@StartBracket@@+5.5@@EndBracket@@. }
7. Nxe5
{ Equalizing material, attacking the pinned Knight on  c6  with two minor pieces. }
7... Be7
{ The most played continuation, trying to bring the King to safety next move.   7...Be6  is the alternative, in view of  8.Bxc6+  bxc6  9.Nxc6  @@StartBracket@@+4.0@@EndBracket@@. }
8. Bxc6+
{ 8.Nxc6  is not good in view of  8...Qd7  @@StartBracket@@+2.0@@EndBracket@@. }
8... bxc6 9. Nxc6
{ Forking Queen and Bishop. Black is totally lost @@StartBracket@@+8.0@@EndBracket@@. }
