1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 { Ruy López } 3... Nf6 { Berlin Defense } 4. d3
{ Protecting  e4  . } 4... Ne7
{ Mortimer Trap, A rather dubious move, leaving  e5  unprotected on purpose. }
5. Nxe5
{ This is a poor move, because  e5  is a poisoned pawn as we will see in the next couple of moves. }
5... c6
{ If the Bishop moves, Black can give check on  a5  with his Queen and capture the Knight in the center next move. }
6. Nc4 { A sneaky move!  6...cxb5  ends in a smothered mate  7.Nd6#! } 6... Ng6
{ Black is not really in a hurry. The dark-squared Bishop now covers  d6  . }
7. Ba4 { Retreating the Bishop. } 7... b5
{ Forking two minor pieces with a pawn. Black is better @@StartBracket@@-2.5@@EndBracket@@. }
