7. exd5 cxd5 8. Bb5+ Bd7 { Blocking the check while attacking  b5  . } 9. Re1+
Be7
{ This one seems a logical move, but it is in fact a blunder.   9...Ne7  would have been better. That way, the Bishop on  f8  still protects the pawn on  g7  . }
10. Qg4
{ What a move! Attacking  d4  and  g7  . The Bishop on  d7  can't capture the Queen since it is pinned to the King. }
