3... Bg4 { Pinning the Knight to the Queen, not the most accurate move. } 4.
dxe5 { Exchanging pawns. } 4... Bxf3
{ A zwischenzug. But trading pieces isn't the most accurate idea. } 5. Qxf3
{ Capturing the Bishop, activating the Queen. } 5... dxe5
{ Equalizing material. } 6. Bc4
{ Threatening checkmate on  f7  .   6.Qb3  is also a good move. } 6... Nf6
{ Avoiding checkmate, but overlooking White's next tactical shot. } 7. Qb3
{ Attacking  b7  while threatening to capture  f7  . } 7... Qd7
{ The most played move in this position, but not the best one! } 8. Qxb7
{ Grabbing a free pawn, attacking the Rook in the corner. } 8... Qc6
{ The reason why Black played Qd7 on the previous move: Attacking the Queen while defending the Rook on  a8  . But there is a problem with this move... }
9. Bb5
{ Pinning the Queen to the King! Black will lose the Queen and the game @@StartBracket@@+9.0@@EndBracket@@. }
