5. Bd2 { Developing the dark-squared Bishop, defending the Knight on  c3  . }
5... Qxc5 { Equalizing material. } 6. Nd5
{ By far the best move in the position. White threatens Bb4 next move. } 6...
Bxb2 { Grabbing a pawn, attacking the Rook. A very poor move! } 7. Rb1
{ Bringing the Rook into safety, attacking the Bishop. } 7... Bd4
{ Attacking the pawn on  f2  . } 8. Bb4 { Counter-attacking is best here! }
8... Bxf2+
{ 9.Kd2?  fails to  9...Qd4+  10.Bd3  Nf6  11.Qf3  Nxd5  12.exd5  @@StartBracket@@+0.0@@EndBracket@@. }
9. Ke2 Qd4 { Offering a Queen trade. Black has nothing better... } 10. Bc3
{ Attacking the Queen and the Rook behind her! } 10... Qxd1+
{ Exchanging Queens. } 11. Rxd1
{ White will win one of Black's Rooks in the next couple of moves @@StartBracket@@+3.5@@EndBracket@@. }
