1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 { Petrov Defense } 3. Nxe5 { Classical Variation } 3... Qe7
{ Attacking the Knight in the center with an early Queen move. } 4. d4
{ Defending the Knight. } 4... d6 { Attacking the Knight with a pawn. } 5. Nf3
{ Retreating the Knight. } 5... Qxe4+ 6. Be2
{ Developing a piece while blocking the check. } 6... Be7 7. Nc3
{ Attacking the Queen. Black now faces an important decision, because two normal looking Queen moves are huge blunders.   Although  7.O-O  is slightly better objectively speaking, I like  7.Nc3  a lot. Black can go wrong in several ways. }
7... Qg6
{ 7...Qc6  is equally bad since it runs into  8.Bb5  @@StartBracket@@+7.5@@EndBracket@@. }
8. Nh4
{ Believe it or not, but Black's Queen is trapped while it is under attack. Most White players missed this winning move @@StartBracket@@+7.5@@EndBracket@@! }
