4. Nf3 Nxe4 5. Qe2
{ Cozio Attack or Lasker Attack, Attacking the Knight on  e4  while pinning it to the King. }
5... Qe7 { Defending and unpinning the Knight. } 6. d3
{ Attacking the Knight once more. } 6... Nf6 7. Nc3 Bg4
{ Pinning the Knight to the Queen while developing the Bishop. } 8. Be3
{ The best move in the position. } 8... Nc6 9. h3 { Chasing away the Bishop }
9... Bh5 { A poor move, you will see why in an instant! } 10. g4
{ Attacking the Bishop again. } 10... Bg6 11. g5
{ Moving forward again, attacking the Knight. } 11... Nd7
{ A natural looking move with huge consequences. This is the move most players play. But  11...Kg8  is better @@StartBracket@@+2.0@@EndBracket@@. }
12. Nd5 { Attacking the Queen while threatening a Knight fork on  c7  . } 12...
Qd8
{ Retreating the Queen, defending  f7  . But it is already too late to limit the damage! By moving the Queen, Black is now vulnerable to a discovered check. }
13. Nxc7+ { Forking King and Rook anyway! } 13... Qxc7 14. Bb6+
{ Discovered check while attacking the Queen with the Bishop. } 14... Kd8 15.
Bxc7+
{ White won a lot of material and should be winning easily from here @@StartBracket@@+5.5@@EndBracket@@. }
