Bxd5+ { This move is preferred to a Queen trade:  8.Qxd5+  Qxd5  9.Bxd5+ } 8...
Kg7 9. Qe5+ Qf6 10. Qxf6+
{ Because of our next move, a killer move, trading Queens is the best move in this position! }
10... Kxf6 11. b4
{ What a move! The point is to play Bb2 next move, skewering King and Rook. Because the Bishop on  d5  is guarding  g8  , Black will not be able to save the Rook. The reason why  b4  is better than  b3  , is because Black could try  c6  followed by  b5  , trying to chase the Bishop away from the  a2  -  g8  diagonal. Because the pawn is on  b4  instead of  b3  , the Bishop can safely go to  b3  . White is winning @@StartBracket@@+7.5@@EndBracket@@. }
