1. e4 e5 2. f4 { King's Gambit } 2... exf4 { King's Gambit Accepted } 3. Nf3
{ King's Knight Gambit } 3... Be7 { Cunningham Defense } 4. Bc4
{ A solid developing move. } 4... Bh4+
{ Checking White's King, trying to force White to give up his castling rights. }
5. Kf1 { White's best move. } 5... Be7
{ 'Mission accomplished', the Bishop now can retreat to a safer square. } 6. d4
{ Taking control of the center, while attacking the pawn on  f4  . } 6... g5
{ Defending  f4  , but overlooking White's next move... } 7. Ne5
{ Moving forward with the Knight, attacking  f7  twice. } 7... Nh6
{ Defending  f7  , right? } 8. Qh5
{ Attacking both the Knight on  h6  and the pawn on  f7  . Black is lost. }
8... d5 { The only move to stay in the game. } 9. Bxd5
{ 9.Qxh6??  throws away the win in view of  9...dxc4  @@StartBracket@@-2.0@@EndBracket@@. }
9... Qd6 { Defending the Knight on  h6  with the Queen. } 10. h4
{ Undermining Black's pawn chain by attacking  g5  , the least advanced pawn in the chain. White is better @@StartBracket@@+3.5@@EndBracket@@.   Stockfish 13 doesn't like  10.Bxf7+  all that much, in view of  10...Kd8  @@StartBracket@@+2.0@@EndBracket@@. }
