1. e4 e5 2. f4 { King's Gambit } 2... exf4 { King's Gambit Accepted } 3. Nf3
{ King's Knight Gambit } 3... g5 { Preparing  g4  . } 4. h4 g4
{ Pushing the pawn forward, attacking the Knight. } 5. Ne5
{ Kieseritzky Gambit, the best square for the Knight: attacking  g4  with two pieces. }
5... d6 6. Nxg4 Be7
{ A sneaky move, attacking  h4  . That pawn will fall next move. } 7. Bc4
{ A natural looking move and commonly played in this position.   7.d4  ,  7.Nf2  or  7.Qf3  would have been more accurate. }
7... Bxh4+
{ Black is a pawn up and has two excellent Bishops. White's king is vulnerable due to the lack of pawns on the kingside. Black is better @@StartBracket@@-2.0@@EndBracket@@. }
*

