1. e4 e5 2. f4 { King's Gambit } 2... exf4 { King's Gambit Accepted } 3. Nf3
{ King's Knight Gambit } 3... g5 { Preparing  g4  . } 4. Bc4
{ Developing a piece, preparing to castle. } 4... g4
{ Scaring away the Knight. } 5. Ne5 { Salvio Gambit, attacking  f7  twice. }
5... Qh4+
{ Punishing White's risky play with a check @@StartBracket@@-2.0@@EndBracket@@. }
6. g3
{ Again not the most accurate move...   Better would have been  6.Kf1  . } 6...
fxg3 7. Qxg4 { A fatal mistake, played hundreds of times! } 7... g2+
{ Check, and threatening to capture the Rook while making a new Queen! } 8.
Qxh4 gxh1=Q+
{ Black has a big edge @@StartBracket@@-9.0@@EndBracket@@.   A possible continuation:  9.Ke2  Be7  10.Bxf7+  Kd8  . }
