{ This blunder is asking for the Knight to get pinned... } 5. Qe2
{ Pinning the Knight to the King. } 5... Qe7
{ Unpinning the Knight while defending it. } 6. Nd5
{ The absolute best move in this position: Attacking the Queen and the pawn on  c7  . }
6... Qe5
{ Defending both the Knight and the  c7  pawn, while attacking White's Knight in the center. }
7. Nbc3 { Defending the Knight on  d5  and putting pressure on  e4  . } 7... c6
{ A desperate move. White has to be careful, because there is only one move that will lead to a big advantage. }
8. d4
{ Attacking the Queen. She can no longer defend both the Knight and the  c7  square @@StartBracket@@+5.0@@EndBracket@@.   A possible continuation is  8...Qxd4  9.Nxe4  cxd5  10.Nd6+  Kd8  11.Qe8+  Kc7  12.Nb5+  , forking King and Queen. }
