{ Damiano Defense. Protecting the pawn on  e5  in this way is a blunder. } 3.
Nxe5
{ Capturing  e5  anyway. Because the f-pawn moved, the pawns on Black's kingside are seriously weakened. }
3... Qe7
{ Actually Black's best move. But why play  f6  if you know that it isn't good to capture the Knight with the pawn? }
4. Nf3 { The best square for the Knight to go to. } 4... d5
{ Attacking White's center pawn. Black's pawn on  d5  can't be taken since White's pawn on  e4  is pinned to the King. }
5. d3 { The only move to keep an advantage. } 5... dxe4
{ Trading a pair of pawns. } 6. dxe4 Qxe4+ 7. Be2
{ Blocking the check while developing the Bishop. This position is similar to the previous position, except that there are no longer pawns on the d-file @@StartBracket@@+2.0@@EndBracket@@. }
