[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Bc5 { Busch-Gass Gambit, A dubious gambit. } 3. Nxe5
{ Capturing a free center pawn. } 3... Qh4
{ The most played move in this position, threatening checkmate on  f2  and a capture on  e4  . }
4. d4
{ Most players played  4.Qf3  in this position, defending the pawn on  e4  . But  4.d4  is better: Expanding in the center, while kicking back Black's Bishop. }
4... Qxe4+
{ Capturing a pawn with check while attacking  d4  . This move scares a lot White players. But their fear is unjustified. }
5. Be3
{ Blocking the check while defending the pawn on  d4  . Black's Bishop still is under attack. White's plan is easy: Bring your pieces out and get ready to castle. Black is obliged to react to White's moves, e.g. Nc3 or Nd2 @@StartBracket@@+3.5@@EndBracket@@. }
