Nbd2
{ Attacking the pawn once more, a move with excellent practical winning chances. It is important to put the Knight on  d2  .   6.Nc3  would allow  6...Bb4  , pinning the Knight to the King. }
6... Bf5 { The only remaining possibility for Black to defend  e4  . } 7. dxe4
Bxe4 { 7...Nxe4  would allow  8.Nh4  @@StartBracket@@+5.0@@EndBracket@@. } 8.
Ng5 { A brilliant move, putting the Knight en prise. } 8... Qxg5
{ Capturing a free piece? } 9. Nxe4
{ The point of this move is that White threatens to capture Black's Queen and a checkmate-in-2  (after Nxf6+ and Qe8#)  . }
9... Qe5 10. Nxf6+
{ Check, and remember that the Queen is pinned to the King, so Black has to recapture with the pawn. }
10... gxf6 11. Bf4 { Again, the Queen is pinned to the King! } 11... Qxe2+ 12.
Bxe2
{ White has the Bishop pair and a more solid pawn structure @@StartBracket@@+2.5@@EndBracket@@. }
