{ Jaenisch Counterattack, Attacking the pawn on  e4  . That pawn can't be defended by the Knight on  b1  , since the  c3  and  d2  squares are occupied by pawns... }
4. d4 { Expanding in the center. } 4... exd4 5. e5
{ Attacking the Knight on  f6  . } 5... Ne4
{ Not a bad move. But it would be easier to defend Black's position after  5...Nd5  . }
